'''''Mother Earth''''' (Italian: '''''Terra madre''''') is a 1931 Italian [[drama film]] directed by [[Alessandro Blasetti]] and starring [[Leda Gloria]], [[Sandro Salvini]] and [[Isa Pola]]. It was made at the [[Cines Studios]] in [[Rome]]. Along with Blasetti's other early films, it shows a strong influence of [[Cinema of the Soviet Union|Soviet]]-style [[socialist realism|realism]].<ref>Reich & Garofalo p.224</ref> A country [[landowner]] decides to sell up and move to the city, but later has a change of heart. It was part of [[Kingdom of Italy#Fascist regime .281922.E2.80.931943.29|Fascist Italy]]'s promotion of [[rural]] over [[Urban area|urban]] values.

==Cast==
* [[Leda Gloria]] as Emilia 
* [[Sandro Salvini]] as Il duca Marco 
* [[Isa Pola]] as Daisy 
* [[Olga Capri]] as La governante della tenuta 
* [[Vasco Creti]] Nunzio, Il massaro, padre di Emilia 
* [[Carlo Ninchi]] as Il commandatore Bordani 
* [[Franco Coop]] as Silvano, un contadino
* [[Raimondo Van Riel]] as Un contadino nella taverna 
* [[Giorgio Bianchi (director)|Giorgio Bianchi]] as Il cortegiatore di Daisy 
* [[Ugo Gracci]] as L'aiutante del massaro
* [[Umberto Sacripante]] as Il contadino idiota

